Lead.text: 2016-07-06 18:54fileIn the east, Daenerys Targaryen, the last scion of House Targaryen, rules with her three dragons as queen of a city built on dust and death.
2016-07-06 18:54fileBut Daenerys has thousands of enemies, and many have set out to find her.
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>Fleeing from Westeros with a price on his head, Tyrion Lannister, too, is making his way to Daenerys.
2016-07-06 18:54fileThere, Jon Snow, 998th Lord Commander of the Nights Watch, will face his greatest challenge.
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>for Lodey, Trebla, Stego, Pod, < / p >

2016-07-06 18:54file< / emphasis > Whereas < emphasis>Feast < / emphasis > focused on events in and around Kings Landing, on the Iron Islands, and down in Dorne, < emphasis>Dance < / emphasis > takes us north to Castle Black and the Wall (and beyond), and across the narrow sea to Pentos and Slavers Bay, to pick up the tales of Tyrion Lannister, Jon Snow, Daenerys Targaryen, and all the other characters you did not
2016-07-06 18:54fileOthers were slain by those who had been their brothers-in-arms when they marched south with Mance Rayder, the King-Beyond-the-Wall.
2016-07-06 18:54file< p >< emphasis>Mance is fallen, < / emphasis > the survivors told each other in despairing voices, < emphasis>Mance is taken, Mance is dead.

2016-07-06 18:54file< / emphasis > Harmas dead and Mance is captured, the rest run off and left us, Thistle had claimed, as she was sewing up his wound. Tormund, the Weeper, Sixskins, all them brave raiders.
2016-07-06 18:54file< emphasis>I was Varamyr Six-skins, who broke bread with Mance Rayder.

2016-07-06 18:54fileHis sleeping pelts and woolen smallclothes, his sheepskin boots and fur-lined gloves, his store of mead and hoarded food, the hanks of hair he took from the women he bedded, even the golden arm rings Mance had given him, all lost and left behind.
2016-07-06 18:54fileIf Mance is dead, the free folk are doomed.
2016-07-06 18:54fileHe rode to battle on the back of a snow bear thirteen feet tall, kept three wolves and a shadowcat in thrall, and sat at the right hand of Mance Rayder.
2016-07-06 18:54file< emphasis>It was Mance who brought me to this place.
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>Before Mance, Varamyr Sixskins had been a lord of sorts.
2016-07-06 18:54fileMance would have cursed him as well, but Mance was slain or captured.

2016-07-06 18:54file< / emphasis > It would be good to feel warm again, though it made him sad to think that he would never see the green lands, the warm lands beyond the Wall that Mance used to sing about. The world beyond the Wall is not for our kind, Haggon used to say. The free folk fear skinchangers, but they honor us as well.
2016-07-06 18:54fileOrell had been slain by the turncloak crow Jon Snow, and his hate for his killer had been so strong that Varamyr found himself hating the beastling boy as well.
2016-07-06 18:54fileHe had known what Snow was the moment he saw that great white direwolf stalking silent at his side.
2016-07-06 18:54fileThe gift was strong in Snow, but the youth was untaught, still fighting his nature when he should have gloried in it.
2016-07-06 18:54fileTyrion marked time by the comings and goings of the cabin boy who brought the meals he did not eat.

2016-07-06 18:54fileThe boy always brought a brush and bucket too, to clean up. Is this Dornish wine? Tyrion asked him once, as he pulled a stopper from a skin. It reminds me of a certain snake I knew.

2016-07-06 18:54fileHe was an ugly boy, though admittedly more comely than a certain dwarf with half a nose and a scar from eye to chin. Have I offended you? Tyrion asked, as the boy was scrubbing. Were you commanded not to talk to me?
2016-07-06 18:54fileTell me that. Jaime had made mention of the Free Cities, but had never said which one. Is it Braavos?
2016-07-06 18:54fileMyr? Tyrion would sooner have gone to Dorne.
2016-07-06 18:54file< emphasis>Myrcella is older than Tommen, by Dornish law the Iron Throne is hers.
2016-07-06 18:54fileI will help her claim her rights, as Prince Oberyn suggested.
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>Oberyn was dead, though, his head smashed to bloody ruin by the armored fist of Ser Gregor Clegane.
2016-07-06 18:54fileAnd without the Red Viper to urge him on, would Doran Martell even consider such a chancy scheme?
2016-07-06 18:54fileOld Bear Mormont said the Nights Watch had need of men like Tyrion.
2016-07-06 18:54fileJanos Slynt would see to that.

2016-07-06 18:54file< p>The cabin boy wet his brush and scrubbed on manfully. Have you ever visited the pleasure houses of Lys? the dwarf inquired. Might that be where whores go? Tyrion could not seem to recall the Valyrian word for whore, and in any case it was too late.
2016-07-06 18:54fileTyrion had some Braavosi and a smattering of Myrish.
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>Sleep had never come easily to Tyrion Lannister.
2016-07-06 18:54file< / emphasis > It was all beyond his reach, Tyrion knew now.
2016-07-06 18:54file< / emphasis > The crossbow < emphasis>thrumm < / emphasis>ed, Lord Tywin sat back down, and Tyrion Lannister found himself waddling through the darkness with Varys at his side.
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>Varys had escorted him through the tunnels, but they never spoke until they emerged beside the Blackwater, where Tyrion had won a famous victory and lost a nose.
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>Wherever whores go. Tyrion had warned his father not to say that word.
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>I killed Shae too, he confessed to Varys.
2016-07-06 18:54fileVarys had saved him from a headsmans sword, but only because Jaime had compelled him.
2016-07-06 18:54file< emphasis>Jaime no, better not to think of Jaime.
2016-07-06 18:54fileTyrion told him to be quiet and kicked feebly as a huge bald sailor tucked him under one arm and carried him squirming to the hold, where an empty wine cask awaited him.
2016-07-06 18:54fileTyrion pissed himself in his struggles, for all the good it did.
2016-07-06 18:54fileAnother cask slammed into his, and Tyrion bit his tongue.
2016-07-06 18:54fileTyrion gasped greedily and tried to stand, but only managed to knock the cask over sideways and spill himself out onto a hard-packed earthen floor.
2016-07-06 18:54fileHe reminded Tyrion of a dead sea cow that had once washed up in the caverns under Casterly Rock.
2016-07-06 18:54fileI like that in a dwarf. When the fat man laughed, his flesh bounced so vigorously that Tyrion was afraid he might fall and crush him. Are you hungry, my little friend?
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>Thirsty. Tyrion struggled to his knees. And filthy. < / p >
2016-07-06 18:54fileAny friend of my friend across the water is a friend to Illyrio Mopatis, yes. < / p >
2016-07-06 18:54file< p >< emphasis>And any friend of Varys the Spider is someone I will trust just as far as I can throw him.
2016-07-06 18:54fileNo sooner did Tyrion lower himself into the hot water and close his eyes than he was fast asleep.
2016-07-06 18:54fileTyrion shook the last drops off and waddled over patterned Myrish carpets as soft as new spring grass.
2016-07-06 18:54fileAwkwardly he climbed the window seat and flung the shutters open to see where Varys and the gods had sent him.
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>When he heard the door opening behind him, Tyrion turned to confront his fat host. This is Pentos, yes? < / p >

2016-07-06 18:54file< p>The fat man stroked one of the prongs of his oiled yellow beard, a gesture Tyrion found remarkably obscene. Slavery is forbidden in Pentos, by the terms of the treaty the Braavosi imposed on us a hundred years ago.
2016-07-06 18:54fileStill, they will not refuse you. Illyrio gave a ponderous half bow. But now my little friend must excuse me.
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>Yes, my fat friend, Tyrion replied.
2016-07-06 18:54fileShould a day ever dawn when Illyrio Mopatis saw more profit in a dead dwarf than a live one, Tyrion would find himself packed into another wine cask by dusk.
2016-07-06 18:54file< / emphasis > That it would arrive he did not doubt; Cersei was not like to forget him, and even Jaime might be vexed to find a quarrel in Fathers belly.
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>Wherever whores go, he heard Lord Tywin say once more, and once more the bowstring < emphasis>thrum < / emphasis>med.
2016-07-06 18:54file< emphasis>None will dare refuse you, < / emphasis > Illyrio claimed, but somehow Tyrion did not think he meant these two.
2016-07-06 18:54fileBoth were near as fat as Illyrio, with teats that were larger than his head.
2016-07-06 18:54file< / emphasis > Lord Tywin might have been niggardly with his approval and affection, but he had always been open-handed when it came to coin.
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>Tyrion left the fat women to their loaves and kettles and went in search of the cellar where Illyrio had decanted him the night before.
2016-07-06 18:54fileIn the end, Tyrion chose a cask of strongwine marked as the private stock of Lord Runceford Redwyne, the grandfather of the present Lord of the Arbor.
2016-07-06 18:54fileTyrion filled a cup, and a flagon for good measure, and carried them up to the gardens to drink beneath those cherry trees hed seen.
2016-07-06 18:54fileTyrion pictured how his sisters head might look up there, with tar in her golden hair and flies buzzing in and out of her mouth.
2016-07-06 18:54file< emphasis>Yes, and Jaime must have the spike beside her, < / emphasis > he decided.
2016-07-06 18:54fileTyrion knew eunuchs when he saw them.

2016-07-06 18:54fileTyrion settled on a stone bench with his flagon. Tell me, how far should I trust Magister Illyrio? The name made her look up. That far? Chuckling, he crossed his stunted legs and took a drink. I am loath to play whatever part the cheesemonger has in mind for me, yet how can I refuse him?
2016-07-06 18:54fileI could make rather a lot of mischief in Dorne with Myrcella.
2016-07-06 18:54file< emphasis>I cannot seem to hold a wife for very long, < / emphasis > Tyrion reflected.
2016-07-06 18:54file< / emphasis > Or better yet, he should have asked his father. Wherever whores go, Lord Tywin said.
2016-07-06 18:54fileTyrion pushed himself off the bench and went to fetch it.
2016-07-06 18:54fileMagister Illyrio expects you at table within the hour. < / p >
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>She poured for him. Magister Illyrio said that I am to scrub your back and warm your bed.
2016-07-06 18:54file< / emphasis > That he had fucked many a woman who loathed the very sight of him, Tyrion Lannister had no doubt, but the others had at least the grace to feign affection.
2016-07-06 18:54file< / emphasis > Even Lord Tywin had not been afraid, though Tyrion had held a crossbow in his hands. Do you moan when you are being fucked? he asked the bedwarmer.
2016-07-06 18:54file< emphasis>I could live for years on his rings, < / emphasis > Tyrion mused, < emphasis>though Id need a cleaver to claim them.
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>Come sit, my little friend. Illyrio waved him closer.
2016-07-06 18:54fileTyrion Lannister had lived all his life in a world that was too big for him, but in the manse of Illyrio Mopatis the sense of disproportion assumed grotesque dimensions.
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>Did you enjoy the girl I sent you? Illyrio asked. If I had wanted a girl I would have asked for one. < / p >
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>I kill kings, hadnt you heard? Tyrion smiled evilly over his wine cup. I want no royal leavings. < / p >
2016-07-06 18:54fileLet us eat. Illyrio clapped his hands together, and serving men came running.
2016-07-06 18:54fileThe sight of it all made Tyrion feel queasy, but he forced himself to try a spoon of soup for the sake of politeness, and once he had tasted it he was lost.
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>As he was sucking the meat off the bones of his quail, he asked Illyrio about the mornings summons.
2016-07-06 18:54fileIllyrio reached for a piece of the crackling, dipped it in a plum sauce, and ate it with his fingers.
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>Slavers Bay is a long way from Pentos. Tyrion speared a goose liver on the point of his knife.
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>This is so, Illyrio agreed, but the world is one great web, and a man dare not touch a single strand lest all the others tremble.
2016-07-06 18:54fileMore wine? Illyrio popped a pepper into his mouth. No, something better. He clapped his hands together.

2016-07-06 18:54fileHe placed it in front of Tyrion, and Illyrio leaned across the table to remove the lid. Mushrooms, the magister announced, as the smell wafted up. Kissed with garlic and bathed in butter.
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>No, no. Magister Illyrio pushed the mushrooms back.

2016-07-06 18:54file< p>Did she indeed? He remembered the cook, the flour on her hands, heavy breasts shot through with dark blue veins. That was kind of her, but no. Tyrion eased the mushroom back into the lake of butter from which it had emerged.
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>You are too suspicious. Illyrio smiled through his forked yellow beard.
2016-07-06 18:54fileOiled every morning to make it gleam like gold, Tyrion suspected. Are you craven?

2016-07-06 18:54file< p>Here as well. Illyrio Mopatis reached for his wine cup. Yet when a guest plainly wishes to end his own life, why, his host must oblige him, no? He took a gulp. Magister Ordello was poisoned by a mushroom not half a year ago.
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>You mistake me, Tyrion said again, more loudly.
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>You have nothing, finished Magister Illyrio, but we can change that. He plucked a mushroom from the butter, and chewed it lustily. Delicious. < / p >
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>The mushrooms are not poisoned. Tyrion was irritated.
2016-07-06 18:54fileWhy should I wish you ill? Magister Illyrio ate another. We must show a little trust, you and I. Come, eat. He clapped his hands again. We have work to do.
2016-07-06 18:54fileTyrion refused the swan, which reminded him of a supper with his sister.
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>The lords of the Seven Kingdoms did make rather much of their sigils, Tyrion had to admit. Very well, he conceded. A Lannister is not a lion.
2016-07-06 18:54fileYet I am still my fathers son, and Jaime and Cersei are mine to kill. < / p >

2016-07-06 18:54file< p>How odd that you should mention your fair sister, said Illyrio, between snails. The queen has offered a lordship to the man who brings her your head, no matter how humble his birth. < / p >
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>It was no more than Tyrion had expected. If you mean to take her up on it, make her spread her legs for you as well.
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>I would sooner have mine own weight in gold. The cheesemonger laughed so hard that Tyrion feared he was about to rupture. All the gold in Casterly Rock, why not? < / p >
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>Just so. The magister covered his mouth and belched a mighty belch. Do you think King Stannis will give it to you?
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>Stannis might well grant me Casterly Rock, said Tyrion, but for the small matter of regicide and kinslaying.
2016-07-06 18:54fileBut why would you think I mean to join Lord Stannis? < / p >
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>Stannis is at the Wall? Tyrion rubbed at his nose. What in seven bloody hells is Stannis doing at the Wall? < / p >
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>Tyrion was beginning to suspect that a certain freckled washerwoman knew more of the Common Speech than she pretended. My niece Myrcella is in Dorne, as it happens.
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>Even a kinslayer is not required to slay < emphasis>all < / emphasis > his kin, said Tyrion, wounded. Queen her, I said.
2016-07-06 18:54fileDorne might rise for Myrcella, but Dorne alone is not enough.
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>Magister Illyrio wiped sweet cream from his mouth with the back of a fat hand. The road to Casterly Rock does not go through Dorne, my little friend.

2016-07-06 18:54fileOn the first day of each new year he must deflower the maid of the fields and the maid of the seas. Illyrio leaned forward, elbows on the table. Yet should a crop fail or a war be lost, we cut his throat to appease the gods and choose a new prince from amongst the forty families. < / p >
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>Not Stannis.
2016-07-06 18:54file< / emphasis > Stronger than Tommen, gentler than Stannis, with a better claim than the girl Myrcella.
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>Fine words. Tyrion was unimpressed. Words are wind.
2016-07-06 18:54fileDaenerys Targaryen awaited him upon the ebon bench that she had made her throne.
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>Your Grace, said Ser Barristan Selmy, the lord commander of her Queensguard, there is no need for you to see this. < / p >
2016-07-06 18:54fileShe had been dreaming of a house with a red door when Missandei woke her.
2016-07-06 18:54fileThey had been given to her when she wed Khal Drogo.
2016-07-06 18:54fileIt was Drogo who had given her the pelt she wore, the head and hide of a < emphasis>hrakkar, < / emphasis > the white lion of the Dothraki sea.
2016-07-06 18:54fileSer Barristan pulled back the bloodstained shroud.
2016-07-06 18:54fileGrey Worm lowered the torch, so she might see.
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>Your Grace, Ser Barristan said, there was a harpy drawn on the bricks in the alley where he was found < / p >
2016-07-06 18:54file< p> drawn in blood. Daenerys knew the way of it by now.

2016-07-06 18:54file< p>Even those who lack a mans parts may still have a mans heart, Your Grace, said Grey Worm. This one has been told that your servant Stalwart Shield sometimes gave coin to the women of the brothels to lie with him and hold him. < / p >
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>Six or more, said Ser Barristan. From the look of his wounds, they swarmed him from all sides.
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>Gracious queen, said Grey Worm, his killers had forced the genitals of a goat down the throat of your servant Stalwart Shield.
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>The first, Ser Barristan warned, but not the last. < / p >
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>It shall be as Your Grace commands, said Grey Worm.
2016-07-06 18:54fileSer Barristan Selmy remained behind.

2016-07-06 18:54fileSo Dany had dispatched her tiny < emphasis>khalasar < / emphasis > to subdue the hinterlands, under the command of her three bloodriders, whilst Brown Ben Plumm took his Second Sons south to guard against Yunkish incursions.
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>The most crucial task of all she had entrusted to Daario Naharis, glib-tongued Daario with his gold tooth and trident beard, smiling his wicked smile through purple whiskers.

2016-07-06 18:54fileIf Daario could convince the Lhazarene to reopen the overland trade routes, grains could be brought down the river or over the hills at need but the Lamb Men had no reason to love Meereen. When the Stormcrows return from Lhazar, perhaps I can use them in the streets, she told Ser Barristan, but until then I have only the Unsullied. Dany rose. You must excuse me, ser.
2016-07-06 18:54file< / emphasis > She had read that in one of the books Ser Jorah had given her as a wedding gift. You should be hunting with your brothers.
2016-07-06 18:54file< / emphasis > Then she would fly as Aegon the Conqueror had flown, up and up, until Meereen was so small that she could blot it out with her thumb.

2016-07-06 18:54fileMeereens queen must be a lady of Old Ghis. Brown Ben Plumm, the captain of the Second Sons, had put it more succinctly. Man wants to be the king o the rabbits, he best wear a pair o floppy ears. < / p >
2016-07-06 18:54file< emphasis>Some Aegon, but which one?
2016-07-06 18:54fileAegon would have been closer to my age than Viserys.
2016-07-06 18:54file< / emphasis > Dany had only been conceived when Aegon and his sister were murdered.
2016-07-06 18:54fileTheir father, her brother Rhaegar, perished even earlier, slain by the Usurper on the Trident.
2016-07-06 18:54fileHer brother Viserys had died screaming in Vaes Dothrak with a crown of molten gold upon his head.
2016-07-06 18:54fileMirri Maz Duur had been the first, Ser Jorah the second.
2016-07-06 18:54file< emphasis>Or will it be someone I would never suspect, Ser Barristan or Grey Worm or Missandei?
2016-07-06 18:54fileReznak, see what one thousand honors may accomplish. Clutching her < emphasis>tokar, < / emphasis > Daenerys swept past them down the broad marble stair.

2016-07-06 18:54fileThe little scribe had a sweet, strong voice. <emphasis>All kneel for Daenerys Stormborn, the Unburnt, Queen of Meereen, Queen of the Andals and the Rhoynar and the First Men, < / emphasis > Khaleesi < emphasis>of Great Grass Sea, Breaker of Shackles, and Mother of Dragons.
2016-07-06 18:54fileHe also had a gift. Cleon the Great sends these slippers as a token of his love for Daenerys Stormborn, the Mother of Dragons. < / p >
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>Magnificence, prompted Reznak mo Reznak, will you hear the noble Hizdahr zo Loraq? < / p >
2016-07-06 18:54fileHizdahr zo Loraq had grabbed them up with both hands, and now owned most of the fighting pits in Meereen.
2016-07-06 18:54fileA very limber man was Hizdahr zo Loraq.
2016-07-06 18:54fileHizdahr zo Loraq might be worth a careful look.
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>By midday Daenerys was feeling the weight of the crown upon her head, and the hardness of the bench beneath her.
2016-07-06 18:54fileThe crown had given her a headache, and her buttocks had gone to sleep. Ser Barristan, she called, I know what quality a king needs most. < / p >
2016-07-06 18:54fileBrown Ben says there are red wolves in the hills outside the city, and jack-als and wild dogs.
2016-07-06 18:54file< emphasis>The more they eat, the larger they will grow, < / emphasis > Ser Barristan had warned her, < emphasis>and the larger they grow, the more theyll eat.

2016-07-06 18:54file< p><emphasis>All kneel for Daenerys Stormborn, the Unburnt, Queen of Meereen, Queen of the Andals and the Rhoynar and the First Men, < / emphasis > Khaleesi < emphasis>of Great Grass Sea, Breaker of Shackles, and Mother of Dragons, < / emphasis> cried Missandei in her high, sweet voice.
2016-07-06 18:54fileDany glimpsed Ser Barristan sliding closer, a white shadow at her side.
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>Reznak, Ser Barristan said quietly, hold your tongue and open your eyes.
2016-07-06 18:54fileSnow crunched beneath his paws.
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>It landed on Jon Snows chest with a < emphasis>thump < / emphasis > and a scrabbling of claws. <emphasis>SNOW!
2016-07-06 18:54fileGet your feathers out of my face. Jon wriggled an arm out from under his blankets to shoo the raven off.
2016-07-06 18:54file< / emphasis> Jon filled his fist with a pillow and let fly, but the bird took to the air.

2016-07-06 18:54fileThe pillow struck the wall and burst, scattering stuffing everywhere just as Dolorous Edd Tollett poked his head through the door. Beg pardon, he said, ignoring the flurry of feathers, shall I fetch mlord some breakfast? < / p >

2016-07-06 18:54file< p>Roast raven, Jon suggested. And half a pint of ale. Having a steward fetch and serve for him still felt strange; not long ago, it would have been him fetching breakfast for Lord Commander Mormont.
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>Three corns and one roast raven, said Dolorous Edd. Very good, mlord, only Hobbs made boiled eggs, black sausage, and apples stewed with prunes.
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>Later. Breakfast could wait; Stannis could not. Any trouble from the stockades last night? < / p >
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>Good. A thousand wildlings had been penned up beyond the Wall, the captives Stannis Baratheon had taken when his knights had smashed Mance Rayders patchwork host.

2016-07-06 18:54file< p>They had free folk drifting in most every night, starved half-frozen creatures who had run from the battle beneath the Wall only to crawl back when they realized there was no safe place to run to. Was the mother questioned? Jon asked.

2016-07-06 18:54fileStannis Baratheon had smashed Mance Rayders host and made the King-Beyond-the-Wall his captive but the wildlings were still out there, the Weeper and Tormund Giantsbane and thousands more.
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>Burning dead children had ceased to trouble Jon Snow; live ones were another matter.
2016-07-06 18:54file< / emphasis > The words had been murmured by one of the queens men as Maester Aemon had cleaned his wounds.
2016-07-06 18:54fileJon had tried to dismiss them as his fever talking.

2016-07-06 18:54fileAemon had demurred. There is power in a kings blood, the old maester had warned, and better men than Stannis have done worse things than this. < emphasis>The king can be harsh and unforgiving, aye, but a babe still on the breast?
2016-07-06 18:54file< / emphasis > Robb had died at the Twins, betrayed by men hed believed his friends, and his wolf had perished with him.
2016-07-06 18:54fileBran and Rickon had been murdered too, beheaded at the behest of Theon Greyjoy, who had once been their lord fathers ward but if dreams did not lie, their direwolves had escaped.

2016-07-06 18:54fileMormonts raven watched with shrewd black eyes, then fluttered to the window. Do you take me for your thrall? When Jon folded back the window with its thick diamond-shaped panes of yellow glass, the chill of the morning hit him in the face.
2016-07-06 18:54fileWith Stannis in the Kings Tower and the Lord Commanders Tower burned to a shell, Jon had established himself in Donal Noyes modest rooms behind the armory.
2016-07-06 18:54file< / emphasis > Jon moved the cup aside and read the parchment once again.
2016-07-06 18:54fileEach night he walked atop the Wall with Lady Melisandre, and during the days he visited the stockades, picking captives out for the red woman to question.
2016-07-06 18:54file< / emphasis > This would not be a pleasant morning, Jon feared.
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>I think I can find the Kings Tower by myself. Jon hated having guards trailing after him everywhere he went.
2016-07-06 18:54fileJon stopped to watch a moment as Horse pressed Hop-Robin back toward the well.
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>Well fought, Jon said to Horse, but you drop your shield too low when pressing an attack.
2016-07-06 18:54file< emphasis>Kings men in one corner and queens men in another, < / emphasis > Jon did not fail to note, < emphasis>but only a few.
2016-07-06 18:54file< p >< emphasis>Boy < / emphasis > was not the worst of the things that Jon Snow had been called since being chosen lord commander.
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>Jon remembered Ygritte, crying.
2016-07-06 18:54file< p>You will excuse me. Jon showed them his back.
2016-07-06 18:54file< emphasis>My command, < / emphasis > Jon Snow reflected ruefully, < emphasis>as much a ruin as it is a strong-hold.

2016-07-06 18:54file< p>Above the Kings Tower the great golden battle standard of House Baratheon cracked like a whip from the roof where Jon Snow had prowled with bow in hand not long ago, slaying Thenns and free folk beside Satin and Deaf Dick Follard.

2016-07-06 18:54fileTwo queens men stood shivering on the steps, their hands tucked up into their armpits and their spears leaning against the door. Those cloth gloves will never serve, Jon told them. See Bowen Marsh on the morrow, and hell give you each a pair of leather gloves lined with fur. < / p >
